   “damage”  means  death  or  personal  injury,  or  any  loss  of  or 
damage to any property, including land, as the case may require;

(b)  in the case of a substance which is not manufactured but 
is  won  or  abstracted,  the  person  who  won  or  abstracted 
it;

(d)  instructions  for  or  warnings  with  respect  to  doing  or 
refraining  from  doing  anything  with  or  in  relation  to 
the  product;

(ii)  from facts ascertainable by him with the help of 
appropriate expert advice which it is reasonable 
for  him  to  seek:

(i)  where  section  68  applies,  the  time  when  the 
producer supplied the product to another person; 
and

(a)  if his conduct, whether in connection with his duties as 
a  member  of  the  Council  or  otherwise,  has  been  such 
as  to  bring  discredit  to  the  Council;

(a)  to advise the Minister on any aspect related to advertisement, 
including  advertisement  in  contravention  of  Part  II  of 
this Act;

(a)  if his conduct, whether in connection with his duties as 
a  member  of  the  Tribunal  or  otherwise,  has  been  such 
as  to  bring  discredit  to  the  Tribunal;

(i)  the  entitlement  of  any  person  under  a  will  or 
settlement,  or  on  any  intestacy  (including  a 
partial  intestacy);

(ca)  which may be lodged by a consumer relating to aviation 
service as defined in the Malaysian Aviation Commission 
Act  2015  [Act  771];

(d)  that the price or other consideration paid or supplied by 
the  consumer  or  any  other  person  be  refunded  to  the 
consumer  or  that  person;

(i)  that interest be paid on any sum or monetary award at a 
rate  not  exceeding  eight  per  centum  per  annum,  unless 
it  has  been  otherwise  agreed  between  the  parties;

(a)  to provide the Assistant Controller, within the period and 
in  the  manner  and  form  specified  in  the  notice,  any 
information  referred  to  in  subsection  (1);

(b)  to take samples of goods or records found in the premises 
for the purpose of ascertaining, by testing or otherwise, 
whether  the  offence  has  been  committed;

(a)  search  for  and  seize  any  goods,  thing,  book,  document, 
record  or  other  article  that  is  reasonably  believed  to 
furnish  evidence  of  the  contravention  of  this Act;

(b)  take samples of any goods or thing found in the premises 
for the purpose of ascertaining, by testing or otherwise, 
whether  an  offence  has  been  committed;  and

(b)  may require the person whom the Assistant Controller has 
reasonable cause to suspect is using or to have used the 
computer  in  connection  with  that  information  or  data;

(a)  he did not know or suspect that the disclosure made under 
paragraph (1)(b) was likely to prejudice the investigation; 
or

(cb)   the  disclosure  is  made  in  circumstances  where  the 
information  provided  is  framed  in  such  a  manner  that 
the  source  of  the  information  could  not  be  ascertained;

(aa)  the offence was committed without his knowledge or that 
he took reasonable precautions to prevent its commission; 
and

(a)  if his conduct, whether in connection with his duties as a member of 
the  Committee  on Advertisement  or  otherwise,  has  been  such  as  to 
bring  discredit  to  the  Committee  on Advertisement;
